<TrainingDetailsVTwo ID="x68549" Name="News Front" Layout="default-training_v2.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">News Front</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">News portal of the most recent department news articles</Abstract><TrainingImage type="imagefile" label="Page Type Image" hidden="false" readonly="false" required="false" Expanded="true" AlternateText="" Border="" HSpace="" VSpace="" Width="300" Height="337" Alignment="">Internal_Use/Ingeniux_Training/Template Thumbnails/NewsroomFront.jpg</TrainingImage><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Body Copy" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<h3>Proper Use</h3>
<p>Create one News Front page per office as the main landing page for finding current news. This page will not need direct editing thereafter. News Stories are automatically added to the list, sorted chronologically by publish date.</p>
<p>The only item that is needed is the selection of a '<a href="x15031.xml">News Navigation Component</a>' (you may need to create one). This will point to a folder or page where all '<a href="x15005.xml">News Article</a>' under it will display in the center column.</p>
<p>You can add contact information and highlighted links to the left column. You can also add information to a right column which include: A list of department publications, Facebook link, YouTube link, RSS link, Twitter link, and a Facebook feed. If no items are filled in for the right column then the center column will expand to fill the space.</p>
<p> </p>
<h3>Intended Authors</h3>
<p>All advanced authors (editors).</p>
<p> </p>
